article.headline: Florida A&M 66, North Florida 65
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Leslie Robinson scored 21 points and Florida A&M survived a furious North Florida rally in the final three minutes to post a 66-65 win over the host Ospreys on Wednesday. Robinson, who missed his first start of the season for disciplinary reasons, came off the bench early in the first half and hit 3-of-7 shots from beyond the 3-point line. He connected on all four of his 3-point shots in the second half to finish 7-of-11 from the field. Florida A&M (6-6) held a 14-point lead at 64-50 with 3:02 left in the game when North Florida mounted a rally. The Ospreys (1-10) finished with a 15-2 run and had a chance to win the game in the closing seconds, but reserve guard Jonson Yousefzadeh missed a jumper with four seconds remaining. The Rattlers aided North Florida's comeback by missing their final seven free throw attempts in the last 69 seconds. North Florida, which was without leading scorer Rashad Williams, was led by center James Grimball with 20 points.
